[SN]TITLE[SN]
Derbyshire v Durham: Alex Hughes scores century to set up tricky run chase for visitors

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Durham require another 246 runs to beat Derbyshire in an intriguing Division Two encounter at Chesterfield.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The visitors resumed on 274-8 and Barry McCarthy (39) and Paul Coughlin (73 not out) took their ninth-wicket stand to 90, before Durham were all out for 301.
Derbyshire had a first-innings lead of 67 but they slumped to 31-3 in their second, before Alex Hughes (108 not out) saw them to 214 all out.
Needing 282 to win, Durham closed on 36-0 with Michael Richardson on 29.
Derbyshire were frustrated in the morning session as Durham's tail pushed the visitors' total past 300 after being 205-8 on day two.
In reply, Hughes was one of only three Derbyshire players to reach double figures, with Luis Reece making 37 and first-innings centurion Matt Critchley scoring 28.
